The room was quiet. The managersâ€”most of whom respected their bosses and maintained good relationships with the companyâ€™s corporate leadershipâ€”knew their leaders were smart, experienced, and committed to the success of the company. The problem was that no one could understand why this new plan had been implemented.
â€œHas anyone asked?â€ I questioned them.
