â€œThis was something he knew he should have run through me,â€ Gary continued, â€œand he blatantly did not. He made the wrong call, and that set our completion date back several days, costing our company serious capital.â€ In this industry, each day lost on the project could cost hundreds of thousands of dollars.
â€œTell me about your superintendent,â€ I said. â€œWhy do you think he would do that?â€
â€œNo idea,â€ said Gary. â€œHe knows he has to run that call through me. But heâ€™s been in this business way longer than I have, and heâ€™s got a ton of experience. Sometimes he looks at me, and his face says What the hell do you know? Iâ€™m sure he thinks he knows better than me.â€
